-- Saudi State Fund Approves Home Loans Valued at $1.5 Billion
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-01-28T09:23:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-28/saudi-state-fund-approves-home-loans-valued-at-1-5-billion.html
Saudi Arabia ’s state-run  Real Estate
Development Fund  approved 11,000 loans valued at 5.6 billion
riyals ($1.5 billion) to build 13,000 homes, the  Saudi Press
Agency  reported, citing the fund’s director, Mohammed Al-
Abadani.  The loans are the first tranche of loans approved in fiscal
2012, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
